              <link rel="colorSchemeMapping" href="file:///C:/Users/Paige/AppData/Local/Temp/msohtmlclip1/01/clip_colorschememapping.xml" id="ithpg" />
            <p id="iy6of" class="MsoNormal">Paige Douglas is an active chamber and solo musician in Tallahassee, Florida. She is currently a flute performance major at Florida State University (FSU), class of 2026. She frequently performs with FSU’s graduate-level bands and orchestras, and she is currently co-principal of the University Symphony Orchestra. She participated in the Florida Flute Association 2023 and 2024 conferences with the FSU Flute Ensemble.</p>
            <div id="ihyap">
              <br id="iwv7i" />
            </div>
            <p id="iqini" class="MsoNormal">Douglas studies with Dr. Karen Large and Dr. Mary Matthews at FSU. In her hometown of Maryville, Tennessee, she studied with Knoxville Symphony Orchestra member Zach Millwood and previous Maryville College professor of flute Nathalie Simper. </p>
            <div id="i5tq4">
              <br id="iv30i" />
            </div>
            <p id="ifpoo" class="MsoNormal">Alongside her flute studies, Douglas is also an active painter and animator. This February, her work “Glowing” was featured in Blackberry Mountain’s<em id="ii8q9"> Perennial Ties</em> group exhibition. She also collaborated with the Khemia Ensemble to create a series of animations for their show<em id="ilo7e"> all the lives we lived</em>. </p>
            </p>
